- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as CAD is used in computational geometry for solving geometric problems involving polynomial equations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of the CAD algorithm. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possibility as the paper deals with quantifier elimination, which is a logical concept. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as CAD has applications in control theory and robotics.
